SIMPLE: morindin
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: morindin
<hw>mo*rin"din</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A yellow dyestuff (<chform>C27H30O14</chform>) extracted from the
root bark of an East Indian plant (<spn>Morinda citrifolia</spn>) or
from the bark of <spn>Coprosma australis</spn>. The substance is also
found in the fruit of the <spn>Morinda citrifolia</spn>, called
<prodby>noni</prodby>, which is touted by some merchants to have a
stimulatory effect on the immune system. It is a disaccharide derivative
of anthracenedione.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Morinel</ent>⟦br⟧
